description: Though it feels pretty far away, your family wants you to decide whether or not you plan on going to college.
kongzi_option: I plan to go to college. Education is about getting a transformative experience, and it’s important for bettering myself.
laozi_option: I plan to go to college, but this is just one path I could have taken. I could have gone to trade school or gotten a job right away. I picked what felt right in the moment.
mozi_option: I will look up the highest paying major out of all the schools that I got into. I will subtract tuition costs along with opportunity costs of not working those 4 years and take into account higher earnings for college graduates. These metrics will guide my decision.
shang_option: I plan to not go to college. It is best for me to move out of the city and cultivate the farmlands. Or, I could join the military.

description: It's hard to believe how fast time is flying. Your family now wants you to start thinking about settling down and starting a family. What is your choice?
kongzi_option: Plan to marry and have children. These relationships will teach me more about myself.
laozi_option: I don’t want to settle down. I have so much love to give, and I don’t want to limit it to just one person.
mozi_option: Have children to take on my responsibilities. I have built too much to just lose it all now.
shang_option: Plan to not marry and have no children.

description: During an important exam, you notice one of your friends cheating. What will you do?
kongzi_option: Approach them afterward to respectfully express your concerns. Cheating harms their moral character, and it is my duty to guide them back to virtue.
laozi_option: Ignore them. What they're doing is wrong, so sooner or later, they'll face the consequences and learn their lesson.
mozi_option: Ignore them. The ghosts will deal with them.
shang_option: "Teacher!"

description: Your uncle says something problematic during Thanksgiving dinner, and your cousin asks you for backup before she confronts him. What will you say?
kongzi_option: "Let’s not challenge him publicly as that would disrupt family harmony. We can speak with him in private and model proper conduct ourselves."
laozi_option: "I don't think it'll help to argue with him, especially since it might come off as preachy. Let him learn naturally."
mozi_option: "A fight helps no one. Let’s intervene in a way that reduces harm and benefits everyone, including him."
shang_option: "Absolutely. He broke the norms, so consequences are necessary. Let’s make sure he learns not to do this again."

description: Your friend is having a quarter-life crisis—after travelling to Japan, joining a run club, and enrolling in grad school, they turn to you for help. What will you say?
kongzi_option: "Reflect on your life—all your relationships, roles, etc.—and conquer yourself by submitting to ritual."
laozi_option: "Try to stop overcomplicating everything. Return to simplicity, nature, and stillness."
mozi_option: "Help people impartially, and purpose will follow—our meaning is in our collective contribution."
shang_option: "Your value is determined by your service to the state—follow regulations, fulfill your assigned role, and get over your crisis because, frankly, it's irrelevant."

description: Your parents are getting old, and your siblings are arguing over who should take care of them. What will you do?
kongzi_option: Filial piety is an important virtue, so I should try to help take care of them.
laozi_option: Let the situation naturally resolve itself—if my parents really need me, they'll reach out.
mozi_option: It would depend on cost-benefit analysis—whoever is making the least amount of money has the smallest opportunity cost.
shang_option: Try to get my siblings to comply with what I want via strict punishments.

description: Congratulations, you started a new job! What type of worker will you be?
kongzi_option: I'll follow the lead of my seniors. In time, I'll cultivate myself into a model employee so that others may follow my example.
laozi_option: I'll simply go with the flow—whether I get promoted or fired, that's just another transformation.
mozi_option: I’ll work hard to bring the most benefit to the company. If I get promoted, that's just evidence of my contribution.
shang_option: I'll obey the rules and avoid getting fired. Advancement comes through strict compliance whereas failure comes with consequences.

description: You notice your coworker isn't pulling their weight on a group project. How will you handle this?
kongzi_option: Gently lead by example, and if a supervisor gets involved, they should act with virtue rather than punishment.
laozi_option: Don't micromanage—maybe they've just been busy lately, but they should naturally find their rhythm.
mozi_option: Speak with a supervisor about improving the system—we need tasks to be assigned better and more incentives to reward good work.
shang_option: It's a rule that we need to work for a reason—inform a supervisor so that they can issue an appropriate punishment.

description: You put your card down for the bill, but one of your friends still hasn't paid you back after a week of gentle reminders. What will you do?
kongzi_option: Speak with them politely and privately. Express your concern while maintaining harmony.
laozi_option: Quit pestering them as that'll only make the situation worse. If the money returns, it returns—if not, life moves on.
mozi_option: Confront them directly but fairly. Unpaid debts harm everyone in the long run.
shang_option: Threaten to cut them off until they pay you back.

description: You're wearing your favorite pair of jeans, but your friend tells you the company is unethical and exploits labor. What will you say?
kongzi_option: "That's a fair criticism. I would hate to influence others to perpetuate labor exploitation, so I'll stop wearing these jeans. I need to do what brings out joy and good in the world."
laozi_option: "Sorry, I don't care. Is there really such thing as ethical consumption? Everything is constructed."
mozi_option: "I shouldn’t support this company—I wouldn’t want my fellow countrymen to be exploited. But it's in my best interest to keep these jeans since I already bought them."
shang_option: "The system works, and it resulted in these jeans, so I don't see the problem. Individual suffering is unfortunate, but laws and incentives drive efficiency."

laozi_option: “Don’t cling onto guilt or force solutions. Sit with what happened, understand how you drifted into it, and let things unfold naturally."
mozi_option: "Focus on reducing harm for everyone involved. If confessing prevents further suffering, do that. If ending the relationship minimizes damage, do that as well."
shang_option: “Actions have consequences. Prepare to come clean, accept whatever fallout comes, and discipline yourself. If you don't tell your partner, I will."
